  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Change Adaptation and Mittigation Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Based on Denmark&apos;s development support policy &quot;The Right to a Better Life&quot; and the Bangladesh Climate Change Strategy and Action Plan (BCCSAP) this climate change programme will address Bangladesh priorities in both climate change adaptation and climate change mitigation through a focus on green growth.
The programme includes three engagements:
a)Climate Change Adaptation Project with LGED, which funds upgrading of rural infrastructure in Southern Bangladesh. b) Waste to Energy Engagement with IFC, which will facilitate biogas and electricity generation from farm waste. c) Energy Efficiency Engagement with NCCI, which will promote the adoption of energy efficiency in selected industries.</narrative>
  </description>
